President Barack Obama has proclaimed April 12-18, 2015, as National Volunteer Week in the United States. In his proclamation, President Obama recognizes the importance of volunteerism in strengthening society and encourages all Americans to embrace a life of active citizenship by giving back to their communities. He highlights the significant impact volunteers can have in times of tragedy, places of great need, and in their own neighborhoods. The President also mentions the initiatives undertaken by his administration to support and expand national service opportunities, such as AmeriCorps and Senior Corps. He emphasizes that the task of improving the nation does not rest solely on the government but requires the collective effort of all Americans. President Obama calls upon citizens to observe National Volunteer Week by participating in service projects and making service a regular part of their lives.